On May 13, 2022, the President signed two bills into law. The first bill, S. 812, modifies a reporting requirement on Taiwan's participation in the World Health Organization. The second bill, S. 3059, known as the "Courthouse Ethics and Transparency Act," amends the Ethics in Government Act of 1978 to provide reporting requirements for Federal judicial officers and the online publication of their financial disclosure reports. The President thanked Senators Menendez, Inhofe, Cornyn, Coons, Durbin, Grassley, Kennedy, Whitehouse, Cruz, and Ossoff, as well as Representatives Young Kim, Sherman, Ross, Issa, Nadler, Hank Johnson, and Roy for their leadership in these bills.